A '''baller''' is someone who has "made it to the bigtime", or a person who is "living large".  
Ballers spend vast amounts of money on such things as alcohol, classy restaurants/clubs, diamonds, rings, clothing for their loved ones, high-stakes poker and other forms of gambling, and many other things.

In casual language, it is often replaced with "hella b", meaning "hella baller".  It is a compliment, and has taken on a meaning similar to "cool".

The term was widely introduced to to pop culture with the 1995 hit single by [[Skee-Lo]] "I Wish".

