In the medical and science community, this term is taken to mean one who is highly successful, which is determined by the number of times that individual has published in highly respected journals: Nature, Cell, Science etc... Typically to be called a baller, one must publish in one of these magazines at least once a month for three or four consecutive months.

Examples of usage:
"Wow! what a Baller" "My that Dr. So and So is such a Baller"

Adaptations for multiple fields are possible such as: 
"Wow! what a Neuro-Baller" or "Wow! What a Hella-Neuro-Baller"